DTSTAMP:20260720T142028Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270104
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270105
SUMMARY:Deadline: Leon Levy Center for Biography Fellowships 2027-28 (incl.
  Levy/Sloan Science Biography)
DESCRIPTION:Four resident biography fellowships plus the Levy/Sloan Fellows
 hip\, funded by the Alfred P. Sloan Foundation\, for a biography of a figu
 re in science or technology\; separate Sherwin fellowship for nuclear-age 
 history. Open to writers of all nationalities\, with explicit preference f
 or first-time biographers who have not yet held a biography fellowship\, t
 hough mid-career and senior writers are welcome\; independent writers elig
 ible. Fellows join monthly seminars and the center's public events. Apply 
 with CV\, career narrative\, project description\, writing sample and two 
 references (agents\, editors and publishers are discouraged as referees). 
 No application fee.\n\nOrganisation: Leon Levy Center for Biography\, CUNY
  Graduate Center\nLocation: New York City\, USA (in residence at the CUNY 
 Graduate Center\, September to May)\nAward: $72\,000 stipend plus writing 
 space\, full research facilities and research assistance\nDuration: Septem
 ber 2027 to May 2028 (academic year in residence)\n\nMore: https://theleon
 levycenterforbiography.submittable.com/submit?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://theleonlevycenterforbiography.submittable.com/submit?utm_source
 =artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:New York City\, USA (in residence at the CUNY Graduate Center\, Se
 ptember to May)
END:VEVENT
